    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nAn autocmd using `++once` with multiple events fires once per event, not just once in total.\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```lua\nlocal count = 0\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd({\n\t\"BufEnter\",\n\t\"VimEnter\",\n}, {\n\tcallback = function(data)\n\t\tcount = count + 1\n\t\tvim.print(data.event ..\" -> \".. count)\n\tend,\n\tonce = true,\n})\n```\n\n<img width=\"512\" height=\"141\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/28e1bfbb-9ea6-4aa3-8232-2ca55add35b5\" />\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nAs the documentation states, “If ++once is supplied, the command is executed once,” so perhaps “only once” (in total) is the reasonable expectation.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-1858+g5f22cf5af3\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nhave not tried\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWSL2\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
